definitions.text: strange in an interesting or pleasing way
examples: quaint streets of New Orleans, that most foreign of American cities

definitions.text: very strange or unusual; odd or even incongruous in character or appearance; - Bill Beatty; - Sir Walter Scott
examples: the head terminating in the quaint duck bill which gives the animal its vernacular name
came forth a quaint and fearful sight
a vaulted roof supporting old-time chimney pots
